<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Magnolia Flowers</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 20px;
        }

        img.align-left {
            float: left;
            margin-right: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        img.align-right {
            float: right;
            margin-left: 15px;
            border-radius: 8px;
        }

        img.responsive {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            max-width: 250px;
        }

        p {
            overflow: auto;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            img.align-left, img.align-right {
                float: none;
                display: block;
                margin: 10px auto;
                max-width: 80%;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <p>
        <img src="https://i2.pickpik.com/photos/218/994/354/magnolias-flower-blossom-spring-30237a04b14fa2168b7feb14e345d223.jpg" 
             alt="Magnolia Flower" 
             class="align-left responsive">
        <b><i>Magnolia</i></b> is a beautiful flowering plant with large, fragrant blossoms. 
        These trees are known for their early spring bloom and add elegance to gardens and parks worldwide.
    </p>

    <p>
        <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5fdc37ac64d87c40396ca2e5/53a6a9d0-90a5-4fb5-bf68-61c4c0671bb3/012-magnolia-DavetheMage.jpg" 
             alt="Magnolia Blossom" 
             class="align-right responsive">
        Some magnolias, like <i>Magnolia stellata</i> and <i>Magnolia soulangena</i>, bloom before their leaves open, creating a spectacular display. 
        Their elegance and longevity make them a favorite for ornamental planting.
    </p>
</body>
</html>
